 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=x>X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/11/02 6:18:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What's your favourite Nuclear Rocket Concept?</span><hr size=1> This is Tim from over at the projectorion Yahoo! Club.  I have an idea for what sort of system I would like to see: close-cycle nuclear rocket.  Use some sort of molten metal or salt as a heat exchange so that no radiation can escape into the exhaust not to mention it doubling as radiation shielding.  This will allow the rocket to be used on the earth surface.  Also, there will be no need for a special facility to test the rocket in so you save a $ billion.  And it may be possible to use air as the working fluid while it's in the atmosphere giving it more fuel efficiency. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ubestonnet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bestonnet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/11/02 11:34:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What's your favourite Nuclear Rocket Concept?</span><hr size=1> Nuclear Ramjet.  A very good idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ucrwillis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>crwillis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/21/02 12:36:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What's your favourite Nuclear Rocket Concept?</span><hr size=1> My favorite is Nuclear Powered Momentum Exchange. It is capable of sending a 3000 ton spaceship with a crew of 1000 to Mars in 5 weeks.  It is also capable of sending Manned Missions to Jupiter or Saturn in 6 months.  It is the first practical technique for man to visit the outer planets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ubestonnet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bestonnet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/22/02 12:11:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What's your favourite Nuclear Rocket Concept?</span><hr size=1> I'm sceptical of momentum exchange mainly because I don't like the idea of a projectile hitting the craft at high speeds.<br>
